  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to have my previously created accounts easily accessible and imported when installing Status so that i can use my previous accounts without going through the recovery steps.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*:  I have 10 files in my `keystore` folder, all accounts created in the past by Status, Status doesn't Status import any of these when installed (clean install), but imports the one(s) that were used in a previous installation, but not the older ones (dirty install).\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nWhen Status is installed, the previously created accounts in the `keystore` folder get imported to the account list without going through the recovery steps and the account list is showed when opening Status after an installation instead of Console.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nFor a clean install, Console is shown and a new account has to be created first, for a dirty install, the account(s) that were present before the dirty install are shown instead of Console, but other accounts that are stored inside the `keystore` folder don't get shown/imported.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Create an account\r\n- Uninstall Status (for a clean install)\r\n- Install a fresh installation of Status or if you skipped previous step, install a new/different version of Status on top of current installation\r\n- For a clean install, you get shown Console and have to create a new account, for a dirty install, you will get shown account(s) that were previously present before installing on top of a previous installation\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n*Summary*: Check if there are files present at the `keystore` folder, if a file on `keystore` folder matches the format that Status uses to create accounts, import all such files to application's accounts when opening the app for the first time after installation.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.4-11ge5fe1b6+\r\n* Operating System: Android",
